In article <1992May11.040322.21709@microsoft.com>
erich@microsoft.com (Eric Hanchrow) writes:
>how 
>does one
>define a ``random'' stream of bits?

Knuth v.2 has an extensive discussion of randomness.  However, this
isn't really applicable to cryptology, because it's in a "lack of patterns"
context, rather than the "unpredictable even given all past history"
context we need here.

